revision.text:
The '''Cuban Assets Control Regulations''', {{USCFR|31|515}}, are regulations of the [[United States Department of the Treasury]] on July 8, 1963, under the [[Trading with the Enemy Act of 1917]], that general regulate relations between [[Cuba]] and the U.S. and are the main mechanism of domestic enforcement of the [[United States embargo against Cuba]].

It was recently modified by the [[Office of Foreign Assets Control]].<ref>{{USFR|74|46000}}</ref>

